info.senderName: NWS GreenBay (East Central Wisconsin - Green Bay)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 07 at 7:52AM CDT until further notice by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...The National Weather Service in Green Bay WI has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Wisconsin River below Biron Reservoir affecting Wood County. ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM THIS MORNING UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Wisconsin River below Biron Reservoir. * WHEN...From this morning until further notice. * IMPACTS...At 1017.0 feet, Widespread wooded lowland flooding. Water approaches a few homes on South Biron Drive in Biron. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 7:10 AM CDT Thursday the stage was 1017.0 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 7:10 AM CDT Thursday was 1017.0 feet. - Forecast...No forecast is available for this location. - Flood stage is 1017.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued late tonight.
